\text{rate} = 140\scriptsize\text{ (claims per month)} \normalsize \text{ per }12 \text{ hours}
= \frac{140\scriptsize\text{ (claims per month)}}{12\text{ hours}}=\frac{35}{3}\scriptsize\text{ (claims per month)} \normalsize \text{ per} \text{ hour}
(x \text{ hours})\times\left(\frac{35}{3}\scriptsize\text{ (claims per month)} \normalsize \text{ per}\text{ hour}\right)=3000 \text{ claims per month}
\Rightarrow x\times\frac{35}{3}=3000
